Author: jl777c#5810
Content: pushdata4 and 3 are still there, even though consensus rules make it so they really are not needed, just there for completeness

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: there is this thing called varint, which allows to encode various integer sizes based on some special prefix codes, essentially a hard coded huffman tree. and the varint supports up to 4 bytes. my guess is that supporting varint is the reason we have the unused pushdata4
